<br>
FPs are a factor even in long-term (&gt;500 years) storage due to the damage that they may do to the repositories - letting the actinides loose.<br>
<br>
BTW - make sure the numbers used by Fred's kid are for SPENT FUEL. It is a no-no to consider HWL as only reprocessed FPs. Instead of a deeply buried plutonium mine, extracting the actinides creates a plutonium floodplain in commercial flow thru the biosphere. That nasty activity is gradually coming to a end. Finally the world has reached a point where, when someone suggests reprocessing fuel rods, serious red warning flags go up.<br>
<br>
BTW - Chemical waste management is another thankless nasty and boring job that I want no part of.<br>
